.TH SIMPLE-MCP-CLI 1 "November 20, 2025" "0.6" "Simple MCP Manual"
.SH NAME
simple-mcp-cli \- Command-line client for the simple-mcp server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple-mcp-cli
[\fI\-server address\fR] \fIsubcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple-mcp-cli
is a testing and debugging tool for the \fBsimple-mcp\fR server. It allows users
to list and invoke tools and resources directly from the command line.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-server " address"
The address of the \fBsimple-mcp\fR server (default: \fIlocalhost:8080\fR).

.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B list-tools
Lists all tools exposed by the server.
.TP
.BI show-tool " name"
Displays the description of the specified tool.
.TP
.B list-resources
Lists all resources exposed by the server.
.TP
.BI show-resource " uri"
Displays the description of the specified resource.
.TP
.BI resource " uri"
Reads and prints the content of the specified resource.
.TP
.BI tool " name " [ \-\-param " value " ]...
Invokes the specified tool with parameters. Parameters must be prefixed with
double dashes (\-\-).

.SH EXAMPLES
.B List all tools:
.P
.RS 4
simple-mcp-cli list-tools
.RE
.P
.B Get system uptime resource:
.P
.RS 4
simple-mcp-cli resource simple-mcp://system/uptime
.RE
.P
.B Call a tool with a parameter:
.P
.RS 4
simple-mcp-cli tool PackageVersion --package bash
.RE

